.TH MDE-SHELL-MIGRATE-V2 1 "2026-05-19" "MDE 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mde-shell-migrate-v2 \- first-boot migration from v1.x Mackes Shell to v2.0.0 MDE
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mde-shell-migrate-v2
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs from
.B mde-session.service
on first launch after
.B "dnf upgrade"
from a v1.x box. Four named idempotent steps:
.IP 1. 4
.B step_1_import_xfconf_to_settings
\(em walks the locked
.B XFCONF_TO_MDE_KEY
map and pushes each via
.B "mded fleet push-setting <key> <value> --peers all".
.IP 2. 4
.B step_2_remove_xdg_autostart_overrides
\(em removes the MDE-generated overrides under
.I ~/.config/autostart/
that suppressed
.B xfce4-panel
and
.B xfdesktop
(only when they carry
.BR Hidden=true ;
vendor files left alone).
.IP 3. 4
.B step_3_backup_xfce4_config
\(em copies
.I ~/.config/xfce4/
to
.I ~/.config/xfce4.v1x-backup.<timestamp>/
so the operator can recover the pre-rebrand state.
.IP 4. 4
.B step_4_write_default_sway_config
\(em seeds
.I ~/.config/sway/
from
.I /usr/share/mde/sway/
when the user doesn't already have one.
.SH OUTPUT
Logged via
.B systemd-cat -t mde-migrate-v2.
Re-running on an already-migrated box is a no-op exit 0.
.SH SEE ALSO
.B mde-migrate-from-1x(1),
.B mde-session(1)
